Subject: Enron Credit Inc. ("ECI")


Cheryl:


Enron Credit Inc. , a  Delaware corporation, has been created for U.S. debt

trading currently handled by ENA.   As a result, ENA will need to transfer

its brokerage debt positions to Enron Credit Inc. accounts with those

brokers.  The brokers include our favorites:


Bear Stearns Companies

Morgan Stanley & Co. Inc.

Goldman Sachs & Co.


ENA will need to assign its positions by the end of February, 2001.

Richard Sage (London office) will need to see the "sample package" (unanimous

consent, authorized trader list).  Will you please see that an email is sent

to Richard with this information?


We should begin the documentation now.  Let me know if you have any questions.


